1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:55,600
Zoro! What are you doing?!

3
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:57,470
Gotta pose before turning solid.

4
00:01:57,470 --> 00:01:59,640
This is no time to be playing around!

5
00:02:00,270 --> 00:02:03,140
Anyway, do something
about your legs!

6
00:02:03,140 --> 00:02:04,650
It hurts just looking at them!

7
00:02:04,650 --> 00:02:06,060
Then quit looking at it.

8
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:10,440
Only an idiot would believe
cutting off his own legs

9
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:12,530
is the best plan of escape!

10
00:02:12,530 --> 00:02:13,490
You've got it wrong!

11
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:16,370
I was gonna cut 'em off
so we could fight.

12
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:19,450
That's even stupider! Get serious!

13
00:02:19,450 --> 00:02:21,290
Just give it a rest!

14
00:02:21,290 --> 00:02:25,580
Honestly! This just goes to show
that you have zero common sense!

15
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:30,380
We haven't even found
a way out of this situation,

16
00:02:30,380 --> 00:02:34,260
yet both are oblivious
to their present danger.

17
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:41,560
Hey, kiddo. Did you change
your mind about fighting?

18
00:02:41,890 --> 00:02:43,020
Sure did.

19
00:02:43,020 --> 00:02:45,560
It's someone else's turn now.

20
00:02:48,270 --> 00:02:51,940
Mr. 3. They don't seem
concerned at all.

21
00:02:51,940 --> 00:02:56,200
I could say the same about you,
Miss Golden Week!

22
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:58,370
Urgh!

23
00:02:59,370 --> 00:03:01,580
Hey, now's the chance
for your own cool pose.

24
00:03:01,580 --> 00:03:04,960
Mr. Bushido! Please take this
a bit more seriously.

25
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,540
I'm always serious.

26
00:03:06,540 --> 00:03:08,500
You mean always stupid!

27
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:12,630
Like you have any room to talk!

28
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:12,630
It's as if they're mocking us.

29
00:03:12,630 --> 00:03:14,760
This is most irksome!

30
00:03:16,050 --> 00:03:17,300
Alright!

31
00:03:18,050 --> 00:03:22,390
This man doesn't seem
to pose any danger.

32
00:03:22,390 --> 00:03:23,980
Mr. 3!

33
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:27,150
We'll finish him off.

34
00:03:27,150 --> 00:03:28,440
Finish him off?

35
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:31,110
Don't be ridiculous.

36
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:33,070
Just look!

37
00:03:33,070 --> 00:03:38,360
Your attacks didn't even faze him,
and now he's here, alive and well.

38
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:43,160
Evidently, he's a bit more
than you two could handle.

39
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,960
I'll leave the rest of the rabble to you!

40
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:54,840
As for Straw Hat Luffy, I'll add him
to my collection of wax figures.

41
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:59,220
You guys are too damn annoying!

42
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:02,890
You've crossed the line!

43
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:04,270
Time to eat dirt!

44
00:04:09,270 --> 00:04:11,400
Alright! Preparations are complete!

45
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,400
We got your back, Luffy!

46
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:16,400
What? Did you say something?

47
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:18,280
Now you're mine!

48
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:20,950
Candle Lock!

49
00:04:24,990 --> 00:04:26,370
What is that?!

50
00:04:28,580 --> 00:04:29,620
Luffy!

51
00:04:29,620 --> 00:04:31,790
Damn, he got caught already?!

52
00:04:31,790 --> 00:04:32,590
Bonehead!

53
00:04:34,090 --> 00:04:36,920
What's this? It's heavy, like a mallet!

54
00:04:37,670 --> 00:04:39,010
Piece of cake.

55
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:42,510
Now for your hands!

56
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:48,640
Oh! This is perfect!

57
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:50,940
Candle Lock!

58
00:04:59,070 --> 00:05:01,030
Old giant guy!

59
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:03,450
Sorry to bother you!

60
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:06,910
What?! What's he up to?!

61
00:05:16,710 --> 00:05:19,420
Gum-Gum...

62
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:20,840
Mallet!

63
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:26,430
– He did it!
– He did it!

64
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:47,450
Luckily, the mallet
on my legs broke too!

65
00:05:47,990 --> 00:05:48,790
Wha...?

66
00:05:51,370 --> 00:05:52,790
Huh?

67
00:05:52,790 --> 00:05:53,920
Huh?!

68
00:05:57,550 --> 00:05:58,630
Still alive...

69
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,340
We survived...

70
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:05,800
Our situation hasn't changed at all!

71
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:09,430
That was dangerous!
Why didn't you guys run away?

72
00:06:09,430 --> 00:06:12,560
– We can't move! Isn't it obvious?!
– We can't move! Isn't it obvious?!

73
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,400
Oh, for real?

74
00:06:14,730 --> 00:06:17,650
But you guys told me
to break the pillar!

75
00:06:17,650 --> 00:06:22,150
Mr. Bushido, why exactly are we
putting our lives in his hands?!

76
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:25,280
Well, we don't have
a choice in the matter.

77
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:28,160
Plus it looks like
my arms are stuck now.

78
00:06:31,540 --> 00:06:33,040
Hold on..

79
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:36,960
It feels like my body is solidifying
more and more now.

80
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:42,050
I can't... move... anymore.

81
00:06:48,260 --> 00:06:49,760
You fools!

82
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:54,100
With the candles closer to you,
you'll harden that much quicker!

83
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:58,360
Now you will become
my human wax candles posthaste!

84
00:06:59,980 --> 00:07:04,450
Who does that
arrogant bastard think he is?!

85
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:07,990
Hey! You guys are
gonna be wax figures?

86
00:07:07,990 --> 00:07:10,240
That's what we've
been trying to tell you!

87
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:13,160
Just destroy this set, Luffy!

88
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,460
Alright, I'm on it!

89
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:17,790
How dare you get in the way!

90
00:07:18,420 --> 00:07:20,500
Wax-Wax Arts: Harpoon!

91
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:21,500
Exploding Star!

92
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:47,030
Pretty bland.

93
00:07:47,030 --> 00:07:49,030
You don't use
high-quality gunpowder.

94
00:07:49,030 --> 00:07:51,990
He ate... my exploding star?!

95
00:07:56,460 --> 00:07:58,580
This is bad.

96
00:07:59,210 --> 00:08:00,840
It really is fast.

97
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:02,960
Good thing I posed beforehand.

98
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:03,670
Moron!

99
00:08:03,670 --> 00:08:06,630
Luffy, please hurry!

100
00:08:08,180 --> 00:08:10,640
Alright! That pumpkin's
the problem, right?!

101
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,010
Hang on!

102
00:08:12,010 --> 00:08:12,760
Gum-Gum...

103
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,720
It's no use!

104
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:16,430
Candle Wall!

105
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:20,270
Bazooka!

106
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:25,070
Hey! Outta the way!

107
00:08:25,070 --> 00:08:27,950
I believe I just told you
the same thing.

108
00:08:27,950 --> 00:08:32,370
I'd appreciate it if you didn't
interfere with my creative activities.

109
00:08:32,370 --> 00:08:33,530
Candle Lock!

110
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:38,290
I got a mallet!

111
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,330
Gum-Gum...

112
00:08:41,330 --> 00:08:42,460
Drat!

113
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:43,710
Candle Wall!

114
00:08:43,710 --> 00:08:45,420
...Mallet!

115
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:07,610
Hooray! Hooray!

116
00:09:04,150 --> 00:09:05,520
M-Mr. 3...!

117
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:06,570
Impossible!

118
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:12,030
Luffy, hurry and break this set
while there's still time!

119
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:12,950
No.

120
00:09:12,950 --> 00:09:15,030
Quit joking around and hurry!

121
00:09:15,910 --> 00:09:16,660
No.

122
00:09:17,290 --> 00:09:19,120
This isn't the time for your antics!

123
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:21,830
Luffy, please!

124
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:25,170
What... do I do?

125
00:09:25,170 --> 00:09:27,840
I don't wanna save you guys.

126
00:09:31,430 --> 00:09:33,300
What are you saying?

127
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:37,310
Colors Trap.

128
00:09:39,020 --> 00:09:40,270
Hey! Luffy!

129
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:43,900
There's no time! Do something
about this thing already!

130
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:45,520
Yeah... I know.

131
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,440
If you know, then hurry!

132
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:48,610
Come on, Luffy!

133
00:09:49,610 --> 00:09:51,490
I know, but...

134
00:09:51,490 --> 00:09:54,370
But I don't wanna save you.

135
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:56,120
Yeah, you keep saying that!

136
00:09:56,620 --> 00:09:58,620
Meanwhile, we're almost wax figures!

137
00:09:58,620 --> 00:10:00,830
Understand?! We're about to die!

138
00:10:00,830 --> 00:10:01,960
Yeah.

139
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:05,080
But for some reason,
I just don't care anymore.

140
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:07,670
– We need you to start caring!
– We need you to start caring!

141
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:11,470
Dammit!

142
00:10:11,470 --> 00:10:13,130
What the hell's with him?!

143
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:17,560
If he doesn't get moving,
our friends are gonna die!

144
00:10:19,140 --> 00:10:20,600
I'll bring him to his senses!

145
00:10:21,060 --> 00:10:22,180
Let's go, Karoo!

146
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:28,020
Wh-When did you...?!

147
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:29,900
Give it up.

148
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:31,860
He's already fallen into a trap.

149
00:10:31,860 --> 00:10:33,110
That's right.

150
00:10:33,110 --> 00:10:34,820
See where he's standing?

151
00:10:34,820 --> 00:10:36,530
Where he's standing?

152
00:10:39,410 --> 00:10:40,740
What's that?

153
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:42,540
There's a strange black symbol.

154
00:10:43,580 --> 00:10:45,460
What's so important about that?!

155
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:49,210
You're right. It's nothing.
It's just paint.

156
00:10:51,630 --> 00:10:52,760
Paint?

157
00:10:53,510 --> 00:11:01,680
To sum it up, it symbolizes the end
for both you... and your friends!

158
00:11:14,990 --> 00:11:17,110
Karoo! Let's just run for now!

159
00:11:18,820 --> 00:11:20,200
They're flying the coop!

160
00:11:20,830 --> 00:11:21,620
Let's get 'em.

161
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:28,000
Full speed ahead!

162
00:11:32,590 --> 00:11:36,550
Hey, you! W-Wait!
I haven't gotten on yet! Karoo!

163
00:11:39,510 --> 00:11:42,970
Alright! Hey! Stop! Lemme on!

164
00:11:47,980 --> 00:11:53,610
Why the hell are you afraid of me?!

165
00:11:57,950 --> 00:11:59,780
Miss Golden Week!

166
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:01,950
This is your doing!

167
00:12:02,740 --> 00:12:05,960
Colors Trap: Betrayal Black.

168
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:09,080
Touch the black paint,

169
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:13,420
and you'll want to betray your friends,
no matter what they say.

170
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:15,300
What does she mean?!

171
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:17,420
Tell us what happened!

172
00:12:17,420 --> 00:12:21,640
That girl is a realist painter who can
recreate the colors of emotion.

173
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:22,640
Wha...?

174
00:12:23,890 --> 00:12:27,890
Her refined sense of color
can be used to manipulate

175
00:12:27,890 --> 00:12:29,850
those who interact with her paints.

176
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,820
Manipulate?! That's not good!

177
00:12:34,150 --> 00:12:39,030
That simpleminded idiot is
already easy enough to manipulate!

178
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:42,990
Then... can't he just
step off the paint?

179
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:45,450
Luffy! Get away from there!

180
00:12:45,450 --> 00:12:46,580
No, don't!

181
00:12:46,580 --> 00:12:47,450
Luffy!

182
00:12:47,450 --> 00:12:51,420
Whatever you do,
do not move from that black circle!

183
00:12:51,420 --> 00:12:52,290
I'm begging you!

184
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,380
Vivi! Why?!

185
00:12:56,380 --> 00:12:59,930
We absolutely do not
want you to save us!

186
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:02,720
No.

187
00:13:04,010 --> 00:13:05,470
I see now.

188
00:13:05,930 --> 00:13:09,440
He's being made to do
the exact opposite of what he's told.

189
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:11,150
Huh?

190
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:15,900
Th-That was a bit weird just now.

191
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:18,940
Alright! Time to save you!

192
00:13:25,740 --> 00:13:27,790
Aw, forget it, you guys!
Gotta laugh!

193
00:13:30,830 --> 00:13:31,870
Why?!

194
00:13:31,870 --> 00:13:32,880
You little...!

195
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,250
Now what?!

196
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:42,760
Colors Trap: Laughter Yellow.

197
00:13:43,090 --> 00:13:45,050
Hey now. Stay still.

198
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:48,720
It's on his clothes!

199
00:13:49,390 --> 00:13:51,980
Luffy! Hurry and take off that vest!

200
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:53,600
N-Never mind that!

201
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:57,400
I just wanna laugh right now!

202
00:14:00,820 --> 00:14:02,780
Son of a...!

203
00:14:02,780 --> 00:14:07,410
At the pace it's raining down,
we won't last another minute!

204
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:16,630
Did you guys only come to fool around?!

205
00:14:20,670 --> 00:14:24,180
Look! When Usopp ran into him,
the paint on his back smudged!

206
00:14:27,470 --> 00:14:30,270
Did she make me
do something again?

207
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:36,360
Hey, you! Knock it off, you jerk!

208
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:39,190
Was my Laughter Yellow a riot?

209
00:14:39,190 --> 00:14:43,030
Shut up! Are you nuts?
That's just dumb!

210
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:45,490
Anyway, I gotta break that pumpkin!

211
00:14:45,490 --> 00:14:46,870
Gum-Gum...

212
00:14:47,620 --> 00:14:50,660
Colors Trap: Bullfight Red.

213
00:14:51,790 --> 00:14:53,500
Bazooka!

214
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:56,380
Where are you aiming?!

215
00:14:56,380 --> 00:14:58,040
You're not allowed to break it!

216
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:59,840
You'll make Mr. 3 angry!

217
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:01,170
What the hell?!

218
00:15:01,550 --> 00:15:05,430
The same way bulls
need to charge at red capes,

219
00:15:05,430 --> 00:15:08,300
you now can't help but attack
my bullfight red mark.

220
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:09,390
Too bad.

221
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:13,850
You suck! I'm gonna send you flying!

222
00:15:14,310 --> 00:15:16,600
Gum-Gum Bazooka!

223
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:20,360
Having fun?

224
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,610
It's no good.

225
00:15:23,610 --> 00:15:26,240
This isn't his kind of fight.

226
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:28,320
His powers are useless here!

227
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:29,660
Here's the finishing touch!

228
00:15:29,660 --> 00:15:32,660
I'll mix the Laughter Yellow
on your back with Sadness Blue!

229
00:15:34,830 --> 00:15:37,880
Colors Trap: Tranquil Green!

230
00:15:42,670 --> 00:15:44,210
This tea is tasty.

231
00:15:45,050 --> 00:15:46,930
– You moron!
– You moron!

232
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:50,050
So, now what?

233
00:15:50,050 --> 00:15:53,560
See? You should've posed
like I told you.

234
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:55,310
Too late for that.

235
00:15:55,310 --> 00:15:57,730
How are you still so calm?!

236
00:16:08,990 --> 00:16:11,910
Damn, they run away fast!

237
00:16:16,330 --> 00:16:18,960
Nose Fancy Double Cannon!

238
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:25,210
You missed!

239
00:16:25,210 --> 00:16:26,510
Way to go, Karoo!

240
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:31,300
My turn!

241
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:33,390
Lethal Lead Star!

242
00:16:36,350 --> 00:16:38,560
We gotta return
to Luffy and the others!

243
00:16:41,310 --> 00:16:43,940
All this running around is pointless.

244
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:45,280
No kidding!

245
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:52,870
I didn't want to use it
on such a small-timer,

246
00:16:52,870 --> 00:16:54,740
but there's no dodging this.

247
00:16:55,740 --> 00:17:00,830
A .44-caliber,
six-shot, flintlock revolver.

248
00:17:00,830 --> 00:17:03,710
A new model from the South Blue.

249
00:17:03,710 --> 00:17:08,170
It's rapid-fire, and when I use it,
no one will see it coming.

250
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:16,140
Luffy's all weird because of the paint
the bad guys mentioned!

251
00:17:16,140 --> 00:17:18,100
They're related somehow!

252
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:22,520
He also had some on his back
when I crashed into him earlier!

253
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:24,020
That's the plan!

254
00:17:24,020 --> 00:17:25,980
I gotta take care of that paint!

255
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:27,570
Hurry!

256
00:17:45,290 --> 00:17:48,090
Such lovely tea.

257
00:17:48,090 --> 00:17:49,170
Huh?

258
00:17:50,050 --> 00:17:52,930
Luffy! What are you doing?!

259
00:17:55,260 --> 00:18:01,390
Such... lovely... tea...

260
00:18:01,690 --> 00:18:05,360
What are you doing, you dumbass?!

261
00:18:09,230 --> 00:18:11,450
It's all over for you.

262
00:18:11,450 --> 00:18:13,740
This ability is second to none.

263
00:18:14,490 --> 00:18:16,490
Lethal Fire Star!

264
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:31,300
How incompetent! He missed
his target and hit his friend!

265
00:18:33,260 --> 00:18:35,510
Aren't there supposed to be bullets?!

266
00:18:39,220 --> 00:18:41,220
Breeze Breath Bomb!

267
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:49,360
Oh yeah, my breath is explosive too.

268
00:18:50,570 --> 00:18:52,070
Dammit...!

269
00:18:52,740 --> 00:18:55,240
This is insane!
He never even had bullets?!

270
00:18:56,070 --> 00:18:58,240
Karoo! You okay?!

271
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:02,330
Hey! Have you come to your senses?!

272
00:19:02,330 --> 00:19:03,620
Y-Yeah...

273
00:19:03,620 --> 00:19:05,920
I'm myself now, thanks!

274
00:19:07,170 --> 00:19:11,380
That attack burned his vest and the trap,
undoing the mental manipulation!

275
00:19:12,840 --> 00:19:15,340
I've had enough of that paint!

276
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:20,810
I won't let you kill anyone else!

277
00:19:22,310 --> 00:19:23,770
Now I'm mad!

278
00:19:26,230 --> 00:19:29,520
Something's not right.
Definitely not right.

279
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:32,190
It's been a long time,
but everyone's still gone.

280
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:36,700
Something must've happened
to Nami, Vivi, and the rest.

281
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:40,910
If so, now's not the time to be
cooking up this lizard.

282
00:19:42,740 --> 00:19:44,750
Nami my sweet! Vivi my love!

283
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:47,540
Nami my sweet! Vivi my love!

284
00:19:48,250 --> 00:19:51,130
Hey! You out there?!

285
00:19:51,130 --> 00:19:52,210
I love you!

286
00:19:58,510 --> 00:20:00,720
What's this?

287
00:20:03,140 --> 00:20:05,310
Who cares if you're mad?

288
00:20:05,310 --> 00:20:07,640
Just look at your friends now!

289
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,860
What's your point?! They're still alive!

290
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:14,360
You sure 'bout that?

291
00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:17,820
When Miss Golden Week
finishes painting them,

292
00:20:17,820 --> 00:20:20,240
they'll be exceptional wax figures!

293
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:22,660
You're too late, Straw Hat!

294
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:26,160
That's correct!

295
00:20:26,910 --> 00:20:31,590
Your time is up, and now you will
taste the bitterness of despair!

296
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:43,310
Deploy!

297
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:52,690
Candle...

298
00:20:53,570 --> 00:20:56,360
Champion!

299
00:21:01,320 --> 00:21:02,660
What's that?

300
00:21:03,030 --> 00:21:08,120
They say he took down someone
worth 42 million berries with that thing.

301
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:10,580
It's Mr. 3's artistic masterpiece!

302
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:13,500
Come, Miss Golden Week!

303
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:17,800
Paint me using your artistry.

304
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:19,720
Can I take a break after that?

305
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:21,220
Yes, of course!

306
00:21:21,220 --> 00:21:23,760
I'd actually prefer
you stay out of this!

307
00:21:23,760 --> 00:21:27,180
Like this, I am invincible!

308
00:21:27,180 --> 00:21:33,060
The wax armor encasing me is
hard as steel, yet so flexible!

309
00:21:33,060 --> 00:21:35,480
My form now...

310
00:21:36,860 --> 00:21:38,860
has no weak point!

311
00:21:42,450 --> 00:21:44,780
S-So cool!

312
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:48,410
This is no time to be
admiring him! Fight!

313
00:21:52,670 --> 00:21:53,750
Alright!

314
00:21:54,460 --> 00:21:57,090
Gum-Gum...

315
00:21:57,090 --> 00:21:58,300
Paint job complete!

316
00:21:58,300 --> 00:21:58,960
Now, then!

317
00:21:59,340 --> 00:22:00,670
...Pistol!

318
00:22:03,340 --> 00:22:07,010
Champ Fight: Field Combine!

319
00:22:09,020 --> 00:22:11,980
Gum-Gum...

320
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:14,440
Stamp!

321
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:20,190
It's no use!

322
00:22:20,530 --> 00:22:23,610
Not good! Luffy's attacks
won't work on something so solid!

323
00:22:29,790 --> 00:22:31,540
Damn! The wax mist!

324
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:35,750
Wax?

325
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:40,630
Yeah!

326
00:22:40,630 --> 00:22:42,260
Why didn't I see it sooner?!

327
00:22:43,510 --> 00:22:47,550
Just the fact that it can mist
means it can melt!

328
00:22:48,140 --> 00:22:50,770
Luffy! Fire melts this guy's wax!

329
00:22:50,770 --> 00:22:53,100
No matter how hard it is,
wax is still wax!

330
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:56,860
Zoro, Master Brogy, and all the others
hardened only moments ago!

331
00:22:56,860 --> 00:22:58,060
We can save them!

332
00:22:58,980 --> 00:23:00,730
What?! For real?!

333
00:23:00,730 --> 00:23:02,110
Yeah. For real.

334
00:23:02,990 --> 00:23:04,910
Don't admit that to them!

335
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:09,330
But even if you realize that now,

336
00:23:09,330 --> 00:23:11,950
you have neither time
nor a chance of winning!

337
00:23:11,950 --> 00:23:14,120
I'd say at most there's thirty seconds!

338
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:17,330
After that, their hearts
will have stopped completely!

339
00:23:17,330 --> 00:23:22,050
Darkness now closes in on them,
their bodies wracked with pain,

340
00:23:22,050 --> 00:23:26,010
as they experience the terror of dying!

341
00:23:28,180 --> 00:23:30,560
We don't need thirty seconds!
I'll save them now!

342
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:32,020
Lethal Fire–

343
00:23:32,020 --> 00:23:34,520
Breeze Breath Bomb!

344
00:23:37,850 --> 00:23:39,190
Usopp!

345
00:23:44,030 --> 00:23:46,780
Did you not hear him say
you have no chance of winning?

346
00:23:51,330 --> 00:23:53,790
Dammit! There's no time!

347
00:23:54,620 --> 00:23:55,410
Just give up!

348
00:24:03,050 --> 00:24:04,050
Listen...

349
00:24:04,050 --> 00:24:05,590
Take this rope...

350
00:24:05,590 --> 00:24:08,130
Oh? This looks like fun!

351
00:24:08,510 --> 00:24:10,430
Whatcha planning?

352
00:24:10,430 --> 00:24:11,850
Can I join in, too?

353
00:24:15,730 --> 00:24:16,850
Karoo.

354
00:24:16,850 --> 00:24:18,350
Run.

355
00:24:18,350 --> 00:24:19,810
Run!

356
00:24:20,190 --> 00:24:23,730
Just keep running around
all the candles!

357
00:24:26,280 --> 00:24:28,200
It's pointless! Give up!

358
00:24:28,910 --> 00:24:30,370
'Scuse me.

359
00:24:31,320 --> 00:24:33,370
Crescendo Stone!

360
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:38,160
Let's see how many kilograms
it'll take until you break!

361
00:24:40,830 --> 00:24:42,290
10 kilograms!

362
00:24:44,050 --> 00:24:45,590
100 kilograms!

363
00:24:48,130 --> 00:24:49,630
200 kilograms!

364
00:24:51,760 --> 00:24:53,350
300 kilograms!

365
00:24:57,100 --> 00:25:00,150
Damn nimble bird!

366
00:25:01,690 --> 00:25:04,110
Give it up! Give it up!

367
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:08,320
They've already become
my masterful works of art!

368
00:25:09,860 --> 00:25:11,450
I don't think so!

369
00:25:11,450 --> 00:25:14,870
I won't lose them
to a weirdo like you!

370
00:25:14,870 --> 00:25:19,160
If fire can melt them,
then I'll just use this thing here!

371
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:20,870
Don't pull! Stop!

372
00:25:20,870 --> 00:25:24,340
Luffy! That small flame
won't work fast enough!

373
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:27,800
Light Karoo's rope on fire!

374
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:29,760
The bird's rope?!

375
00:25:30,130 --> 00:25:31,630
It's a special rope...

376
00:25:31,630 --> 00:25:32,510
Huh?

377
00:25:32,510 --> 00:25:34,680
...soaked in oil!

378
00:25:35,220 --> 00:25:38,060
Okay! Everyone! Wake up!

379
00:25:36,010 --> 00:25:38,060
Hey! Wait! Stop!

380
00:25:38,390 --> 00:25:40,810
Things are gonna heat up,
but bear with it.

381
00:25:41,730 --> 00:25:44,150
Stop!

382
00:25:44,150 --> 00:25:48,570
Ow! Hot!

383
00:25:56,910 --> 00:26:01,710
Yeow! Hot! Hot!

384
00:26:01,710 --> 00:26:03,500
That fire's huge!

385
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:04,960
Are they gonna be okay?!

386
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:09,550
You've done it now, Straw Hat!

387
00:26:09,550 --> 00:26:13,930
How dare you lay waste
to my candle service set!

388
00:26:13,930 --> 00:26:15,390
You'll rue the day!

389
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:21,810
Get back here, you jerks!

390
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:26,940
Dammit!

391
00:26:26,940 --> 00:26:28,480
Take us seriously!

392
00:26:30,610 --> 00:26:33,450
Now you guys have done it!

393
00:26:34,910 --> 00:26:36,780
Playtime is over!

394
00:26:37,660 --> 00:26:41,790
I'm gonna shatter your neck...
into itty bitty pieces!

395
00:26:41,790 --> 00:26:42,750
Lethal...

396
00:26:42,750 --> 00:26:45,460
10,000 Kilo Guillotine!

397
00:26:55,140 --> 00:26:58,100
Was using that much heat
really necessary?

398
00:27:02,350 --> 00:27:04,100
Complaining already?

399
00:27:04,100 --> 00:27:06,560
Show a little gratitude
toward your savior!

400
00:27:06,940 --> 00:27:08,820
You're right. Thanks!

401
00:27:08,820 --> 00:27:10,190
This doesn't seem real!

402
00:27:10,190 --> 00:27:11,780
We're alive!

403
00:27:11,780 --> 00:27:13,780
So the wax melted...

404
00:27:13,780 --> 00:27:15,410
What a pain!

405
00:27:16,030 --> 00:27:19,240
We can't afford
to blow another mission!

406
00:27:20,740 --> 00:27:22,250
Mr. 5!

407
00:27:22,700 --> 00:27:25,580
Lethal Exploding Star!

408
00:27:26,580 --> 00:27:27,580
Are you stupid?!

409
00:27:27,580 --> 00:27:32,550
I'm a human bomb! You've seen
that explosives don't work on me!

410
00:27:32,550 --> 00:27:34,010
You took the bait!

411
00:27:36,180 --> 00:27:39,180
Too bad for you! I'm a liar, you see!

412
00:27:39,180 --> 00:27:42,220
That wasn't an exploding star!
It was a special tabasco star!

413
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:46,810
Spicy!

414
00:27:50,190 --> 00:27:52,900
I already checked
its effectiveness the hard way!

415
00:27:54,990 --> 00:27:56,950
You lousy pirates!

416
00:27:58,990 --> 00:28:01,280
I'll blow you away
with a full-body explosion!

417
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:03,700
There won't even be bone fragments left!

418
00:28:04,290 --> 00:28:06,790
No! Stop!

419
00:28:06,790 --> 00:28:08,370
Usopp!

420
00:28:08,370 --> 00:28:11,500
No! I'm sorry! It won't happen again!

421
00:28:18,260 --> 00:28:20,470
Flaming Oni...

422
00:28:23,390 --> 00:28:25,140
Giri!

423
00:28:41,410 --> 00:28:44,080
Fiery blades. Not too shabby.

424
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:49,120
Zoro!

425
00:29:00,890 --> 00:29:03,140
Hey, good to see you're alive.

426
00:29:04,390 --> 00:29:05,520
Yeah.

427
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:14,570
Master...

428
00:29:16,570 --> 00:29:19,570
That leaves two foes remaining.

429
00:29:21,860 --> 00:29:22,740
Bird!

430
00:29:24,490 --> 00:29:26,160
They won't get off so easy!

431
00:29:27,500 --> 00:29:29,960
Real men don't spoil people's fights!

432
00:29:37,800 --> 00:29:39,840
How good of you to come!

433
00:29:39,840 --> 00:29:43,340
Welcome to my Wax-Wax Mansion!

434
00:29:43,340 --> 00:29:44,720
What is this?!

435
00:29:45,260 --> 00:29:49,850
Well, then. Can you
pick out the real me?

436
00:29:53,810 --> 00:29:57,650
It seems you picked a fight
with the wrong people!

437
00:29:58,030 --> 00:30:03,070
Our team's intellect is unparalleled
in all of Baroque Works!

438
00:30:03,070 --> 00:30:11,620
A brute like you, acting on instinct alone,
has no hope against us!

439
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:14,630
I am Mr. 3.

440
00:30:14,630 --> 00:30:18,500
I flawlessly execute any mission
to which I am assigned.

441
00:30:18,500 --> 00:30:21,550
Now, then! Step inside!

442
00:30:28,430 --> 00:30:34,770
But the moment you turn your back
to me, you'll get a dagger...

443
00:30:38,980 --> 00:30:42,530
right through the heart.

444
00:30:50,040 --> 00:30:52,250
Gum-Gum...

445
00:30:52,250 --> 00:30:54,040
Stamp!

446
00:30:58,340 --> 00:31:00,380
How...

447
00:31:00,380 --> 00:31:02,380
did you know...

448
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:06,010
I was here?

449
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:14,140
Instinct.

450
00:31:45,970 --> 00:31:48,090
Hey, wait a minute!

451
00:31:48,090 --> 00:31:52,930
This is no time for me to be
sipping tea all fancy like!

452
00:31:52,930 --> 00:31:56,690
Nami and the others might be
waiting for me to save them!

453
00:31:58,230 --> 00:32:00,650
Still, though.

454
00:32:00,650 --> 00:32:04,650
Why's a relaxing place like this
in the middle of a jungle?

455
00:32:16,040 --> 00:32:17,120
What's that?

456
00:32:26,670 --> 00:32:28,380
It's a transponder snail.

457
00:32:31,970 --> 00:32:34,140
Hey there!

458
00:32:34,140 --> 00:32:36,270
You've reached The Shit Shack.

459
00:32:36,270 --> 00:32:37,560
Making a reservation?

460
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:43,440
Quit fooling around,

461
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:44,940
you idiot.

462
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:51,320
Aren't you a bit late
with your report?

463
00:32:51,820 --> 00:32:54,290
Oh? Report?

464
00:32:55,620 --> 00:32:58,210
And who might I be talking to?

465
00:32:59,170 --> 00:33:00,420
It's me.

466
00:33:00,420 --> 00:33:02,790
Mr. 0.
